Text.string: Bad feelin' in the air. Or did you just expel a cloud of gut?
Did you catch that Hammerlock and Aurelia are brother and sister? Damn, that is one messy family tapestry.
I used to work for Wainwright's daddy—till Tyreen Calypso gave 'em the kiss of death. Now I work for Wainwright. We'll see once all is said and done.
What do ya think of Eden-6, Vault Hunter? If they call this place paradise, then I've been using the word wrong all these years.
A wise man once said, corporations are like assholes. They ain't any prettier from the inside.
Jakobs Corporation's stood the test of time for three hundred years. To think that some damn ECHOcaster could fell that tree with a kiss of death and a broadcast? Unsettling. That's the word.
I lost a bullet a while back. Sorta fell into this guy who owed me money. Lemme know if you find it.
These bandits are something. I've seen bandits kill over money, over meat... hell, I saw a bandit kill a man once 'cause he was coughing funny. But love? That scares the damn hell outta me.
I hail from Eden-5, myself. You should come by sometime after all this is over. If you're alive... and I'm alive.
We lit the bonfires of the resistance, you and I. Think about that! Someday some little kid with mud on her face might learn the name Clay and say “hero”. Heh, I'm all right with that.
Smooth operator! Aurelia's dead! What are you still doing around here? Ain't got nothing better to do than let the swamp ass gather?
Wainwright's CEO, but there's still a lot of bandits. Good thing we put Jakobs guns back in Jakobs hands.
Been quiet since you left, Vault Hunter. Ya hardly hear the bandits screamin' in the dead of the night anymore.
Heard Pandora's in the mud. Figuratively speaking, that is.
You kill them Calypso Twins yet? No? What the hell you talking to me for?
Wainwright seems to be adjusting to life as CEO. If you ask me, that's a job for a madman and a fool. Now I dabble in both from time to time, but never together.
I'm fixin' to leave Eden. Thought I might take a vacation. Heard Junpai-7 is nice this time of year.
I appreciate the visit, but don't you got better places to be, gunslinger?
So it's come to this, then. The final showdown. Good luck, Vault Hunter.
So falleth the mighty tree—read that in a gift shop I burned down 'cause they owned me money.
You too big of a hero to run jobs with me, smooth operator? I hope not.
Jakobs Corporation restored, a bunch of echocasting nitwits taken down—the cloak of hero clings to ya, Vault Hunter. Don't forget your old friend Clay now that you're a legend.
You know why I say I'm a people person? 'Cause if I said, “Hey, I'm Clay, a cold-blooded gunslinger with a past darker than the bottom of the ocean,”—well, no one would want to talk to me.
This planet ain't no paradise. Sometimes I think the Jakobs family settled here just so they wouldn't have any neighbors... Hmm. Smart, I suppose.
My mama used to tell me, “Clay, I named you that 'cause you're dumb as dirt.” And I always said, “Then why didn't you name me 'Dirt', ma?”
Ya know, sometimes when you've got nothing to say, it's better to say nothin'. Then again, in my experience, the hardest advice to take is your own.

Whew! After all this is over, I'm guessing Wainwright will ask me to stay on and be his advisor, like I did for his daddy. But it ain't the job for me. Corporations are like birthday parties. Someone always craps in the cake. You're just gonna have to trust me on that one.
I might not have been born with a silver spoon in my mouth like Wainwright, but I do just fine. Just fine.
If I had three wishes, you know what I'd wish for? A thousand wishes. Then two planets connected by a water slide. Then dinner.
Whatcha doin' today, Vault Hunter? Me, I'm gonna start recruiting for a... thing... I'm gonna trail off now.
You know why I call you a smooth operator? 'Cause when I point you at a thing, you get the job done.
Keep on fightin', Vault Hunter. Someone has to.
Let's do a job again real soon, yeah?
Not too much to say at the moment. Doin' some thinkin'.
You need somethin'? Just seem to be... standin' around a lot.
People don't expect me to be well-read. But I've finished as many books as I've killed men. Yes sir, I got a cemetery of books up in my brain here.
I shot my gun into the air once. Killed a bird. Pretty one, too. I don't do that no more.
I've been a smuggler since I was in the womb. Would've slipped out into this world sooner if not for that damn umbilical cord.
This swamp ass will be the death of me. This is the only planet where your ass will still sweat if you're sitting in a damn waterfall, and that ain't right.
I took a nap the other day. Woke up and my clothes were gone. And I was wearing 'em when I went to sleep. Damn jabbers.||—Or saurians...
Smooth operator! I don't owe ya money, do I?

Taught myself to read with a dictionary I picked up from a fella who owed me money. Thing is, the letter “M” was missing, so... now when I sit down at a restaurant, I tell the waiter to bring me the food book.
Guns and hope—you remember that, Vault Hunter!
If it ain't the hero of the battle of Reliance! Keep sayin' it over and over, and they'll put it in the history books one day. Mark my word!
There's the newest member of the Rogues. Nice job in the Ambermire, Vault Hunter. Just remember, don't stay in the mud too long or you'll forget about dry land.
Well, look who just strolled in! The gunslinger who restored a Jakobs to the throne!
Now where did I put that gun? Oh, right... [chuckle]
What was I doin'? Oh, right—thinkin'.
[humming]||—Now how did the rest of that go? I should've let that man finish the song before I killed him.
“How you doin', Clay?” You mind your business! “All right Clay, just asking.”
Damn swamp ass.
I can tell you're a real go-getter. And I've got a job for you to go-get.
There's somethin' needs done and my dance card's full. Got a minute?
A Vault Hunter's job is never done. But when you're done, I got a job for ya.
Who goes there?
Smooth operator!
Oh, hey Vault Hunter.
Been too long, friend.
Vault Hunter! Good to see you.
Day just got a little bit brighter. How ya doin'?
Talk fast, we're burnin' daylight.
Lonely is the night. Least it used to be.
Nice night for a fight. Not with you, just in general.
Wanna help me with somethin'?
I could use another pair of hands.
Got a need for a gunslinger.
How's that trigger finger?
Let's get into somethin'.
Don't you got somethin' to do?
You're busy, right?
You're gonna do that thang, right?
I can't call ya smooth operator if ya stop operating, ya dig?
Ain't you got a task that's needs completing?
And so we part.
Later operator!
Be seeing ya.
And we turn another page.
You be careful out there.
Sayonara and goodbye!
See you when I see you.
Catch you later, amigo.
Guess we're done, then.
Fare thee well, gunslinger.
